I want Doctor Strange 2 to:


Be set in New Orleans and the Louisiana bayou...
...where the Nexus of All Realities is opening...
...and Doctor strange teams up with local sorcerer Jericho Drumm (aka Brother Voodoo, but they never call him that) to investigate...
...a series of killings committed by Man-Thing, who is burning people alive for no apparent reason...
...but it's actually because they'e been possessed by Nightmare through their dreams, and he's using them to open the Nexus of All Realities so that he can manifest completely in this world.
Nightmare would be an awesome villain because he really loves psychological manipulation, and Stephen Strange has a lot of psychological weak points. Strange is hyper-rational, but Nightmare is hyper-emotional, so he'd be a great foil.

And Man-Thing is perfect for using as a fake-out villain. Marvel fans who actually know the character (which is not most of them) won't be fooled, but Joe Q. Public will totally buy that he's a monster and be shocked when he's revealed as a mystical guardian.

And you could even throw in Howard the Duck, who gets pulled through the Nexus to Earth.

Oh and use different and creative magic other than Kung fu! Plenty of existing heroes due martial arts. Be creative and have strange using curse spells, demon/ construct summongings, teleportation without sling ring. Start developing his relationships with magic entities like cyttorak by having him gain contracts to use their magic



Push the boundaries of pg-13 by giving derrickson creative freedom to make this a  more horror based non generic sequel mcu series. And make it longer! 2 hours and 30 minutes to three hours !!!

Comment: The movie was good, but it felt like everything was squashed together to fit a time limit. I miss the days when Marvel used to take time to explain everything instead of picking a part in the story and going off from there. The first and second SpiderMan movies with Tobey Maguire are a good example, they start from the beginning and help you build a relationship with the characters. You learn the relationship between Peter Parker and Harry Osbourne, Peter and Mary Jane, Mary Jane and Harry, all of the above and Norman Osbourne and you can almost feel the tension when things start to heat up and fall apart. I mean Uncle Ben was in the movie for less than 30 minutes I think and I felt his death *DR STRANGE SPOILER AHEAD* more than I felt The Ancient Ones death, actually I think I didn't actually really care for her death. With the movies they make these days you cant feel anything like that anymore, and it's a shame because they all have potential.

Title: Doctor Strange Official Trailer 2
Comment:
If you're a parent, don't take kids under 14. Movie wasn't really violent or sexual, nor did it really have adult themes. But it dealt a lot with spirits leaving bodies and interacting. The evil force wasn't a creature or person, but a demonic energy consuming worlds. It was dark & unsettling.
The movie wasn't good. No good fight scenes, no fantastic cinematography, a basic storyline. It was like a cheap sci-fi movie, mixed with a watered down American adaptation of a martial arts film. The setup was perfect: doctor learns that other powers/dimensions exist beyond his scientific imagination. He becomes injured to the point of desperately seeking help in a remote monastery for mastering powers. But it didn't follow through. It was basic & not very entertaining

Title: Doctor Strange Official Trailer 2
Comment:
I am really excited to see this movie.  I've been waiting since I read my first Doctor Strange comic in the late 70's.  I realize I'm dating myself here.  Grace mentioned something though about one of Nolan's movies.  Both Inception and the first Batman movie were great.  I'm a serious Batman fan too.  I cross the great divide a lot.  Any serious research though will show that Nolan "borrowed" heavily from other sources for both these movies.  I'm not surprised that it happened.  Directors have been doing this type of borrowing for a long time.  Grace even did a video where one direct sued another director because of it and surprisingly he won. ;) Borrowing is done heavily; suing is not.  I've noticed a serious problem though growing based on a lot of different youtube channels and internet research.  Example:  apparently at the most recent comic con in San Diego I believe, an artists drawing was given out for free and the artist didn't know about it.  It's great that its free it not great that various companies are taking advantage of artists by not crediting them nor asking their permission.  He said he would have been willing to sign them for free for those who had them.  There are a lot of other examples of this behavior all over youtube and the internet.  Feel free to research this subject yourself.  

Are we all so "dazzled" by great movies that we are willing to turn our backs on the artists who drew our favorite super heroes or the artists that inspire/create/develop new artwork for these movies?  Yet we have no problem in stating a movie was a ripoff simply because it came out afterwards?  I believe it was in the 80" two very similar horror/alien movies came out.  One was based on a great older book.  The movie came out second and even though the first movie borrowed heavily on the original story from the book, the movie based on the original story was claimed to be a ripoff.  Check it out.  It's not hard to figure out which movie I'm talking.  I'm sorry if you feel I'm being to general.  I'm not here to make people believe anything.  Just point things out.  People really need to do their own investigating and come to their own conclusions.  Opinions will be opinions after all.  Thanks

Comment:
Not looking forward to it, I bet it will bomb or at least hopefully.
Been a fan since Ditko, you would think that with all the CGI that they
would be able to duplicate Dr. Strange's psychedelic fantasy worlds,
and characters like Clea, Mordo, Nightmare and of course the Ancient One.

But It will be Dr. Strange only in name and perhaps the costume.
I'm really get sick of these superhero movies where the world will end
or New York is imploding.
Why not have a superhero movie thats not a disaster movie,
thats what made movies like "Kick Ass" and "Deadpool" so great.

I would love a Spider-man movie where Peter Parker is in high school,
with normal problems and some goofy costumed villain comes along,
and he's got to get medicine for his sick aunt.
Just like the comic, thats why those movies suck and Dr. Strange will suck.

Comment: They replaced the comic book's Ancient One,who was originally a very old Tibetan man,with a middle aged White woman because there are too many roles in Hollywood that go to Asians and not nearly enough for White women.I think that's what MARVEL said,anyway.Oh,also Christopher Nolan says "Nice movie,it in no way looks like a rip off of my film INCEPTION.Not in the least.This is all very original."The Wachowski's,Lana and Larry,had this to say "We really like how they came up with such original ways of demonstrating the malleability of physical reality.Honestly,this is like nothing we've done  before.Not even in THE MATRIX."Adrian Lyne reportedly said he was impressed by how deftly they seem to have managed to avoid including any of the darker,more frightening or surreal elements from the original comic book that might make this film less appealing to preschoolers."Unlike my film,JACOB'S LADDER,there appears to be very little imagery that might leave the viewer unsettled,uncertain or jumpy after viewing this movie.Kudos".And lastly,Alex Proyas added "I just wish I'd had such fresh,original ideas when I made my film DARK CITY.That whole scene of a cityscape bending and flowing is like certainly like nothing I've ever seen before."Looks like they've made a future classic.

Comment: This looks VERY good. Way to go Marvel Studios! Funny, I really hated the Wonder Woman and Justice League preview trailers that surfaced this past week.... At first I thought perhaps I'm getting too old for comic movies. Then I see this trailer. This is EXACTLY where comic movies need to venture.I don't see a comic movie, I just see a very interesting SciF film in this trailer. It's something that will appeal to many I think. It's just a trailer, but bearing in mind we are seeing some finished scenes here it's very clear Marvel Studios is creating content many leagues above what WB is doing with the DC Universe. I think what WB are creating with the DC characters feels forced, it feels trite and the characters portrayal from the way they are scripted to the way they acted just feel second rate to what we are seeing from Marvel. I say this as having no allegiance to one over the other. Suicide Squad looks pretty good, but other than that the other films just look second rate to me.

Title: Doctor Strange Official Trailer 2
Comment:
Before I come to what I actually wanted to say, please remember that my comment is meant to express my personal opinion. I do not want to set someone. I'm just commenting on this video, well, because that's what a comment section is for. Also, if you did like this trailer, please keep in mind, that I did not call anyone names, or, let's say, 'butthurt marvel-fanboy/-girl'. To get this out the way, yes I prefer DC. But I enjoyed the X-Men-movies, and especially the Daredevil-TV-series, too, and I'm excitedfor GotG Vol. 2 (First one had magnificent Music, go, buy the soundtrack)! 
I'll give anyone the benefit of the doubt and just presume, that no one here actually is the type, that gets mad at reading an different opinion. But these douchebags exist, and as we all know, debates about topics like Comicbook-adaptations oftenly become very heated very fast. (Especially when these debates take place between fans of certain comicpublishers.) That's just the way it is. It's a mad world. A world where I feel the need to apologize for stating my opinion unasked. Thumbs up if you find that sad. Just kidding, I don't write this because I'm afraid of a small amount of aggressive people on the internet, I just enjoy writing. But seriously, it is a mad world.

Soooo after all that introductory blabla, I shall now release my very important opinion onto an unsuspecting world:
I found this trailer rather... meh. Too much shallow 'meaningful' talk ("I am Death"!!!). Too many confusing (but pretty) Christopher Nolan/Warcraft-lawsuit-CGI. And, hooray, it's a trailer that basically tells an jumpcutted origin story.

But here's the real reason why I'll not see this despite the terrific cast: 
They changed an important character from being tibetan male to caucasian female all just too ensure avoid trouble with their humble costumer China, by not stating, that Tibet is an actual country. That would have been illegal in China, therefore, the movie would have most likely got forbidden. If they had just did that quietly, I would say, that's the business way, I wouldn't mind too much. (I'm a western ignorant after all). BUT not only did they openly admitt that they wanted to appease chinese censoring-agencys, they tried to defend that decision and wanted to sell that casting choice (Tilda Swinton=great actress nonetheless) as an example of Marvels "great sense for diversity". Now, that's what I call offensive! (Perhaps you, dear reader, do not. Feel free to discuss, if you've actually read THIS far. If so, gj)



Also, hey, "I am death" in a Benedict Cumberbatch movie? Smaug for MCU confirmed!
